steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8113s","text":"Thaw the competent cells on ice","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bu1m6","text":"Chill approximately 5 μg (2 μl) of Plasmid DNA in 1.5 mL microcentrifuge tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6vb3o","text":"Add 50 μl of competent cells to the DNA. Mix gently by pipetting up and down or flicking the tube 4–5 times to mix the cells and DNA. Do not vortex.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1488c","text":"Place the mixture on ice for 30 minutes. Do not mix.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"66a1a","text":"Heat shock at 42°C for 30 seconds*. Do not mix.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fpu0h","text":"Add 950 μl of room temperature media* to the tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"btj8","text":"Place tube at 37°C for 60 minutes. Shake vigorously (250 rpm) or rotate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3o8ml","text":"Warm selection plates to 37°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2hgt2","text":"Spread 50–100 μl of the cells and ligation mixture onto the plates.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9qg9a","text":"Incubate overnight at 37°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3be8o","text":"Please note: For the duration and temperature of the heat shock step as well as for the media to be used during the recovery period,","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4hhgf","text":"please follow the recommendations provided by the competent cells’ manufacturer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4m8ti","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dltp0","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"4neps","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fhnaf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"tables","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"cellsMeta":{},"colTitles":["",""],"colWidths":["189","166"],"data":[["PLVX mCherry (HLA-A2)","Amp 50μg/mL"],["Ploc MLANA (MART1)","Blasticidin (50μg/mL)"],["psPAX2","Amp 50μg/mL"],["VSV.G","Amp 50μg/mL"]],"guid":"E3046FE06EDD11EDA368CD88B3A0FC8F","isJexcelDataFormat":true,"legend":"","mergeCells":{},"printData":[["PLVX mCherry (HLA-A2)","Amp 50μg/mL"],["Ploc MLANA (MART1)","Blasticidin (50μg/mL)"],["psPAX2","Amp 50μg/mL"],["VSV.G","Amp 50μg/mL"]],"rowHeights":[23,23,23,23]}}}}

steps.section: Preparation of Liquid Media - LB-Ampicillin Broth and LB-Blasticidin Broth:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"blkbe","text":"Add 20g of LB broth Lennox into 1 liter of distilled water in an Erlenmeyer flask","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of Liquid Media - LB-Ampicillin Broth and LB-Blasticidin Broth:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"850nh","text":"Autoclave the LB broth in the Flask on a wet cycle for 30min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of Liquid Media - LB-Ampicillin Broth and LB-Blasticidin Broth:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6hs3p","text":"Storage of LB in 4ºC is recommended and is good for up to 1 year","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of Liquid Media - LB-Ampicillin Broth and LB-Blasticidin Broth:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"dell6","text":"Ensure that the LB broth has come to room temperature before you add ampicillin","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of Liquid Media - LB-Ampicillin Broth and LB-Blasticidin Broth:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4j1j0","text":"The final concentration of ampicillin in the broth should be 50μg/mL","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of Liquid Media - LB-Ampicillin Broth and LB-Blasticidin Broth:
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"eblv1","text":"LB broth containing ampicillin should be stored at 4ºC for up to 1 month","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7ch2a","text":"LB-Amp Agar and LB-Blasticidin Agar: Each Petri Dish takes about 10mL of LB-Agar so scale the volume accordingly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fibun","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5637u","text":"1 LB agar tablet makes 50mL","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"13sjb","text":"Take 1 tablet and dissolve it in 50mL of distilled water in an autoclaved flask","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6r2v3","text":"Autoclave the LB agar for 30min on a wet cycle","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fibtu","text":"Once the cycle is complete check to make sure that all the agar is dissolved","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c58qt","text":"Allow the LB agar to cool until it is comfortable to the touch (50ºC), a water batch set to 50ºC is useful for this step","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e9sq2","text":"While the agar is cooling label the plates using sharpie for each antibiotic","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3qhps","text":"The final concentration of ampicillin and Blasticidin should be 50μg/mL","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"71mh6","text":"Make sure that the LB agar has cooled to 50ºC as excessive heat will degrade the antibiotics","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3ln6d","text":"a. Ampicillin = Red ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5vomc","text":"b. Blasticidin = Blue","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
